<br>
You have heard much about the guild that calls this platform its headquarters. The Emerald Family, a group of Elves who have dedicated themselves to the preservation of all that is good in these dark times, call this Hall home. The Feir’ Dal vendors that hawk their wares on the platforms near here call this hall the Emerald House. They say that the Hall is enchanted by powerful magics, and that only those of pure heart and noble intention may pass over the threshold. At first you thought this mere superstition, but now, standing before the Emerald House, the hall almost hums with enchantment.<br>
<br>
You sheath your weapons, smooth your garments, and take one final deep breath as you open the doors to the Emerald House. As you take your first step into this Hall, a sense of peace and comfort washes over you. Perhaps, you have finally found a home. Perhaps…<br>
<br>
((The Emerald Family is a roleplaying guild of High Elves, Wood Elves and Half Elves. We have no level requirement nor do we seek any specific class. The only requirement we have is that you are dedicated to playing in a roleplaying environment and that you are one of the races mentioned above. This being said, we take a practical approach to roleplaying, and understand that often, game mechanics prevent you from being in character at all times. We currently have Brothers and Sisters ranging in level from 8 to 57. We are not a raiding guild, although we do organize raids upon targets that we incorporate into stories and plots that we develop in-game and on our messageboard. We try to strike a balance between the areas of EQ that are not as conducive to roleplaying and sharing adventures together that revolve around stories crafted by our Brothers and Sisters. We are run as a democracy with leaders and Officers elected every four months. If you are interested in finding out more about us, please visit our website at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.emeraldfamily.org" target="top">www.emeraldfamily.org</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and leave us a scroll in our forums. I look forward to hearing from you.))<br>
