<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>There once was a maiden so fair.<br>
Who carried the sun in her hair.<br>
Her mother said now child it's time to be wed.<br>
So, you'll marry this big hairy bear.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;One of my favorites that is.&quot;, he says with a grin.  &quot;In fact, it reminds me of a time when I was living in East Karana.  There's a fishing village of northmen there.  Have you ever seen it?  Well, let me just say that they know the meaning of hospitality.  Of course it could have just been my songs and charms mind you.  Then again it could be that my perception is a bit skewed as most of my view of the place was from the arms of a lovely young lass of the village.  She'd carry me around like I was a babe.&quot;  He rambles on as the others roll their eyes. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421" target="top">Trevian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Musical Messenger of Tunare<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.emeraldfamily.org" target="top">The Emerald Family</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=comitas>comitas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/15/03 2:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Emerald Family</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Chuckling quietly to himself, he tries to listen to Trevian's small tale.  As the other adventurers slowly drown out the tale from across the room, Comitas begins to whisper ...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;The activity amongst us is growing once again.  As the seasons change the thirst for adventure sets in amongst us all I guess.  New dungeons arise needing to be cleansed as old dungeons begin to grow due to adventures moving on.  Many tales left to be made, and too many left to be scribed.  Can the blood of this new adventurer be just what we need here?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Once again catching a few lines of random tales be swapped, Comitas leans back against the wall of the hall.  Slowly he starts to remove the bandages to inspect his war-torn hands.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=404554" target="top">Comitas - Soldier of Tunare</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Proud member of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.emeraldfamily.org" target="top">The Emerald Family</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevianemeraldsong>Trevian Emeraldsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/18/03 10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/greg.stafford/TrevBust_tn.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Emerald Family</span><hr size=1> Trevian laughs at his own awful song.  He listens as a rainstorm pours down outside and a strong wind begins to blow.  He turns back to the hearth the always had a warm fire burning inside.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's just like that, eh Comitas?  All around us a storm rages.  Yet there is a fire within us that keeps us going on.&quot;<br>
<br>
He turns to the newcomer again and smiles.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm certain I see great promise in you.  Oh, I'm sure you may have your doubts at times.  There's been times when we've all been chased off by our foes, but through perseverence we've managed to overcome them all.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lke the time we assaulted Ry'gor Keep only to have giants and a griffon descend upon us.  A good amount of calm thinking and a bit of luck saw them off well enough.  No sooner than we did though and somehow Chief Ry'gor came charging out of the keep after us.  We thought we were at the end of our rope, but some how we few skinny elves managed to confuse him and run him around just enough to spare us and bring him to his demise.  Of course, we were also wise enough to watch from a distance as his avengers ran around in confusion before returning to the Keep.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's all part of a grander plan.  Through faith and perseverence we'll see it through.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421" target="top">Trevian Emeraldsong,</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> The Musical Messenger of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.emeraldfamily.org" target="top">The Emerald Family</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
